Frontend UX Principles
Every page should follow the same structure:
Header – Title, description, primary actions.
Context Bar – Current project, sprint, or module information.
Main Content – The core data or workflow.
Quick Actions – Common actions such as create, assign, upload, or review.
Activity Panel (where relevant) – Comments, history, and recent updates.

Final Frontend Vision
KPM should not feel like a generic admin dashboard filled with tables. It should feel like an engineering workspace where planning, collaboration, execution, and delivery happen in one place.
The experience should revolve around four key screens:
Project Workspace – The command center for a project.
Feature Details – The central hub where engineering work happens.
Sprint Board – The team's execution view.
My Workspace – A personalized daily workspace that tells each team member exactly what needs their attention.

